data.title: Dashboard Confessional’s Chris Carrabba Joins Moneen On Stage For “Hands Down”

data.text:
We sure as hell didn’t want last night to end, as Moneen was joined by Dashboard Confessional’s Chris Carrabba on stage in Toronto, ON, Canada!

Welcoming Carrabba to the stage with a hug during the band’s encore, Moneen’s Kenny Bridges joked, “If you got great pals around, you gotta play music with them. I kind of don’t want this night to end, ever. So, Chris, we’re gonna do the 20 minute version of this song.”

As the opening chords of Dashboard Confessional‘s “Hands Down” filled the air, the crowd burst into a cacophony of cheers and applause. Carrabba led the way into the first verse, the audience joining in unison, creating an electrifying harmony that blended seamlessly with Bridges as they united for the track’s infectious chorus. The two vocalists fed off of one another’s energy, smiling between the lines and creating an unforgettable moment for Toronto fans. Check out the full video of Moneen performing with Carrabba below and the band’s full setlist from their show last night below.

November 2, 2023 Moneen Setlist:

Are We Really Happy With Who We Are Right Now?

Start Angry…End Mad

To Say Something That Means Nothing to Anyone at All

With This Song I Will Destroy Myself

Closing My Eyes Won’t Help Me Leave

I Have Never Done Anything for Anyone That Was Not for Me as Well

How to Live With the Thought That Sometimes Life Ends

Life’s Just Too Short Little Ndugu

Thoughts Weigh Heavy…Don’t Get Drowned in the Weight of It All

The Last Song I Will Ever Want to Sing

Encore:

Don’t Ever Tell Locke What He Can’t Do

Tonight, I’m Gone…

Hands Down

The Passing of America
